thread.title: Pharoah in Breeders Cup

author: The Associated Press
title: Pharoah in Breeders Cup
text: The Triple Crown champion American Pharoah will try to close out his career in style by winning the $5 million Breeders’ Cup Classic next week against a loaded field that includes the two-time Breeders’ Cup-winning mare Beholder and Keen Ice, who handed him his only loss this year in the Travers Stakes. A total of 200 horses were pre-entered for the $26 million, 13-race Breeders’ Cup world championships being held at Keeneland in Lexington, Ky., on Oct. 30 and 31.
